entury. However, there is some doubt about her name, as the same saint is venerated in the Orthodox Church as   Marina .  There were several other saintly bearers of the name, including St Margaret of Scotland (  d. 1093 ), wife of  King Malcolm Canmore  and daughter of Edmund Ironside of England. It was also the name of the wife of  Henry VI  of England,  Margaret of Anjou  (  1430–82 ), and of  Margaret Tudor  (  1489–1541 ), sister of  Henry VIII , who married James IV of Scotland and ruled as regent there after his death.  See also  Margery  ,   Marjorie ."],"variants":[{"name":"Margareta","meanings":["From the Latin form of Greek <i>Margarītēs</i>.  See  <b>Margaret</b>   ."]},{"name":"Margaretta","meanings":["Formed from Margaret."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"Margaret Blundeville was born in 1386, in Saltfleetby St Clement, Lincolnshire, England, United Kingdom. She had at least 3 sons and 2 daughters with William Le Newcomen. She died in 1404, in Lincolnshire, England, United Kingdom, at the age of 18."},"et":{"1386–1404":"1386–1404","1370–1404":"1370–1404","1401–1452":"1401–1452","1402–Male":"1402–Surnud","1403–Male":"1403–Surnud","1404–Female":"1404–Surnud","1412–1445":"1412–1445","1404":"1404","1403":"1403","1402":"1402","1401":"1401","1445":"1445","1412":"1412","about 1404":"umbes 1404","about 1402":"umbes 1402","1386":"1386","about 1403":"umbes 1403","1452":"1452","1370":"1370","Saltfleetby Saint Clement, Lincolnshire, England":"Saltfleetby Saint Clement, Lincolnshire, England","Saltfleetby, Lincolnshire, England, United Kingdom":"Saltfleetby St Clement, Lincolnshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Lincolnshire, England, United Kingdom":"Lincolnshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Lincolnshire, England":"Lincolnshire, England"},"fi":{"1386–1404":"1386–1404","1370–1404":"1370–1404","1401–1452":"1401–1452","1402–Male":"1402–Kuollut","1403–Male":"1403–Kuollut","1404–Female":"1404–Kuollut","1412–1445":"1412–1445","1404":"1404","1403":"1403","1402":"1402","1401":"1401","1